    {
        "content": "<p>Oh awesome thank you! I didn't know about the spread notation. I still don't think I understand why it was necessary in this case but not in others.</p>\n<p>For the definitions, I was copying how they are done in mathlib where <code>OrderedCommGroup</code> is <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0c419e32e8cc2b54b3ac18eafa3595cd17659e1e/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Group/Defs.lean#L42\">defined</a>. Basically, copying how mathlib does it, I add the <code>mul_le_mul_left</code> and then add instances for <code>MulLeftMono</code>. Do you think mathlib should switch to the spelling you used as well?</p>",
        "id": 491112587,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1735412346
    }
